ogging(level=logging.INFO)`:\n102:   - [ ] Configure root logger with format\n103:   - [ ] Return logger instance\n104: \n105: ### T010: High-level Code Interpreter client\n106: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n107: - [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__(router_url, workload_manager_url=None, name=None, namespace=\"default\", session_id=None, ttl=3600, timeout=120)`:\n108:   - [ ] Validate `router_url` is provided (arg or `ROUTER_URL` env)\n109:   - [ ] Store config\n110:   - [ ] If `session_id` not provided:\n111:     - [ ] Create `ControlPlaneClient`\n112:     - [ ] Call `create_session()`\n113:     - [ ] Handle failure: delete session, re-raise\n114:   - [ ] Call `_init_data_plane()`\n115: - [ ] Implement `_init_data_plane()`:\n116:   - [ ] Create `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with `session_id`\n117: - [ ] Implement context manager protocol:\n118:   - [ ] `__enter__()`: return `self`\n119:   - [ ] `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `stop()`\n120: - [ ] Implement `stop()`:\n121:   - [ ] Close data plane session\n122:   - [ ] If created session: call `delete_session()`\n123:   - [ ] Close control plane session\n124: - [ ] Implement `execute_command(command, timeout=None) -> dict`: delegate to data plane\n125: - [ ] Implement `run_code(code, language=\"python\") -> dict`:\n126:   - [ ] Write timestamped `.py` file\n127:   - [ ] Execute `python3 <file>`\n128: - [ ] Implement `write_file(path, content)`: delegate to data plane\n129: - [ ] Implement `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`: delegate to data plane\n130: - [ ] Implement `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`: delegate to data plane\n131: - [ ] Implement `list_files(path) -> list`: delegate to data plane\n132: \n133: ### T011: High-level Agent Runtime client\n134: - [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n135: - [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeClient.__init__(router_url, namespace, agent_name, session_id=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n136:   - [ ] Store config\n137:   - [ ] If `session_id` not provided:\n138:     - [ ] GET from invocation base URL\n139:     - [ ] Read `x-agentcube-session-id` from response header\n140:     - [ ] Raise `ValueError` if missing\n141:   - [ ] Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n142: - [ ] Implement context manager protocol:\n143:   - [ ] `__enter__()`: return `self`\n144:   - [ ] `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `close()`\n145: - [ ] Implement `close()`: close underlying session\n146: - [ ] Implement `invoke(payload, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n147:   - [ ] If no `session_id`: raise `ValueError`\n148:   - [ ] Delegate to data plane\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## Verification\n153: \n154: - [ ] All 11 files created and match specifications\n155: - [ ] `pyproject.toml` valid TOML, installable via `pip install -e sdk-python/`\n156: - [ ] All imports resolve: `from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient`\n157: - [ ] Exception hierarchy testable: all custom exceptions inherit from `AgentCubeError`\n158: - [ ] Context managers work: `with CodeInterpreterClient(...) as client:` and `with AgentRuntimeClient(...) as client:`\n159: - [ ] No circular imports between modules\n160: - [ ] All HTTP clients use connection pooling\n161: - [ ] Token resolution from file path works (with graceful fallback)\n162: - [ ] Environment variable fallbacks work for URLs and tokens\n\n(End of file - total 162 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-033: Python SDK — Clients and Exceptions\n\n**Module**: root  \n**Language**: Python  \n**Size**: M (11 files)  \n**Status**: ST-3 completed  \n\n---\n\n## Tasks\n\n### T001: Project scaffolding and package metadata\n- [ ] Create `sdk-python/pyproject.toml` with build-system, project metadata, and dependencies\n- [ ] Verify `name = \"agentcube-sdk\"`, `version = \"0.0.10\"`, `requires-python = \">=3.10\"`\n- [ ] Verify dependencies: `requests>=2.31.0`, dev deps: `pytest>=7.0.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.0.0`\n- [ ] Verify `build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"`\n\n### T002: Package initialization and public API exports\n- [ ] Create `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Export `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient` in `__all__`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"tasks.md","time":{"start":1775899903463,"end":1775899903517}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899903524,"sessionID":"ses_2841e16f7ffeQo8aGKUpSQAL4X","part":{"id":"prt_d7be205c4001fbMuVH6V2mcyTW","messageID":"msg_d7be1fcfe001og0c2ghcn2LfXY","sessionID":"ses_2841e16f7ffeQo8aGKUpSQAL4X","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b88f2bb3a5a64ac6af87e54cd181b7bf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/PLAN.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Implementation Plan — AR-023 through AR-033\n2: \n3: This plan maps Architectural Requirements AR-023 through AR-033 to specific files and implementation details based on the specifications in `./specs/`.\n4: \n5: ## AR Mapping Overview\n6: \n7: | AR | Spec Domain | Package/Path | Description |\n8: |----|-------------|--------------|-------------|\n9: | AR-023 | integrations | `integrations/dify-plugin/` | Dify plugin manifest and provider structure |\n10: | AR-024 | integrations | `integrations/dify-plugin/` | Dify tool schema and implementation |\n11: | AR-025 | example | `example/pcap-analyzer/` | PCAP analyzer FastAPI service |\n12: | AR-026 | deployment | `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart templates for Workload Manager |\n13: | AR-027 | deployment | `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart templates for Router |\n14: | AR-028 | deployment | `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart RBAC and optional Volcano scheduler |\n15: | AR-029 | deployment | `docker/`, `Makefile` | Dockerfiles and build targets |\n16: | AR-030 | ci-cd | `.github/workflows/` | GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines |\n17: | AR-031 | cli-toolkit | `cmd/cli/agentcube/` | CLI pack/build commands |\n18: | AR-032 | cli-toolkit | `cmd/cli/agentcube/` | CLI publish/invoke/status commands |\n19: | AR-033 | python-sdk | `sdk-python/agentcube/` | SDK clients and exception hierarchy |\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## AR-023: Dify Plugin Manifest and Provider Structure\n24: \n25: ### Files to Create\n26: \n27: #### 1. `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py`\n28: **Purpose**: Plugin entrypoint that runs the Dify plugin framework.\n29: \n30: **Logic**:\n31: - Import `dify_plugin.Plugin` and `dify_plugin.DifyPluginEnv`\n32: - Instantiate `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120))`\n33: - Call `.run()` to start the plugin HTTP server\n34: - Block until the host stops the process\n35: \n36: #### 2. `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml`\n37: **Purpose**: Root plugin manifest for Dify platform registration.\n38: \n39: **Structure**:\n40: ```yaml\n41: version: 0.0.2\n42: type: plugin\n43: author: volcano-sh\n44: name: agentcube\n45: label:\n46:   en_US: Agentcube\n47:   ja_JP: Agentcube\n48:   zh_Hans: Agentcube\n49:   pt_BR: Agentcube\n50: description:\n51:   en_US: AgentCube integration for Dify\n52:   zh_Hans: AgentCube 集成\n53: icon: icon.png\n54: icon_dark: icon-dark.png\n55: resource:\n56:   memory: 1048576  # 1MB\n57:   permission:\n58:     tool: true\n59:     model: false\n60:     endpoint: false\n61:     app: false\n62:     storage: false\n63: plugins.tools:\n64:   - provider/agentcube.yaml\n65: meta:\n66:   version: 0.0.2\n67:   arch:\n68:     - amd64\n69:     - arm64\n70:   runner:\n71:     language: python\n72:     version: \"3.12\"\n73:     entrypoint: main\n74:   minimum_dify_version: null\n75: created_at: \"2026-03-24T00:00:00Z\"\n76: privacy: null\n77: repo: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n78: verified: false\n79: ```\n80: \n81: #### 3. `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml`\n82: **Purpose**: Tool provider descriptor that lists tools and points to Python implementation.\n83: \n84: **Structure**:\n85: ```yaml\n86: identity:\n87:   author: volcano-sh\n88:   name: agentcube\n89:   label:\n90:     en_US: Agentcube Code Interpreter\n91:     zh_Hans: Agentcube 代码解释器\n92:   description:\n93:     en_US: Execute code in AgentCube sandboxes\n94:     zh_Hans: 在 AgentCube 沙箱中执行代码\n95:   icon: icon.png\n96: tools:\n97:   - tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml\n98: extra.python.source: provider/agentcube.py\n99: ```\n100: \n101: #### 4. `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py`\n102: **Purpose**: Python implementation of the Dify tool provider class.\n103: \n104: **Logic**:\n105: - Import `dify_plugin.ToolProvider`\n106: - Import `dify_plugin.errors.tool.ToolProviderCredentialValidationError`\n107: - Define class `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider)`\n108: - Implement `_validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None`:\n109:   - Try block: validate that `router_url` and `workload_manager_url` exist in credentials (or implement actual connectivity check)\n110:   - On any exception: raise `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))`\n111: - Return without raising on success\n112: \n113: #### 5. `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`\n114: **Purpose**: Pin Python dependencies for reproducible installs.\n115: \n116: **Content**:\n117: ```\n118: dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n119: agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n120: ```\n121: \n122: #### 6. `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore`\n123: **Purpose**: Specify files to exclude from plugin packaging.\n124: \n125: **Content**:\n126: ```\n127: __pycache__/\n128: *.pyc\n129: .git/\n130: .env\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ## AR-024: Dify Tool Schema and Implementation\n136: \n137: ### Files to Create\n138: \n139: #### 7. `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`\n140: **Purpose**: Tool parameter schema for Dify configuration UI.\n141: \n142: **Structure**:\n143: ```yaml\n144: identity:\n145:   name: agentcube-code-interpreter\n146:   author: agentcube\n147:   label:\n148:     human:\n149:       en_US: Code Interpreter\n150:       zh_Hans: 代码解释器\n151:     llm:\n152:       en_US: Execute Python/JavaScript/TypeScript code in a sandbox\n153:   description:\n154:     human:\n155:       en_US: Run code or commands in an AgentCube sandbox\n156:     llm:\n157:       en_US: Use this tool when you need to execute code safely\n158: parameters:\n159:   - name: router_url\n160:     type: string\n161:     required: true\n162:     label:\n163:       en_US: Router URL\n164:     human_description:\n165:       en_US: AgentCube Router endpoint URL\n166:     llm_description: Base URL for the AgentCube Router service\n167:     form: form\n168:   - name: workload_manager_url\n169:     type: string\n170:     required: true\n171:     label:\n172:       en_US: Workload Manager URL\n173:     human_description:\n174:       en_US: AgentCube Workload Manager endpoint URL\n175:     llm_description: Base URL for the Workload Manager control plane\n176:     form: form\n177:   - name: language\n178:     type: select\n179:     required: false\n180:     label:\n181:       en_US: Language\n182:     human_description:\n183:       en_US: Programming language for code execution\n184:     llm_description: One of python, javascript, typescript\n185:     form: llm\n186:     options:\n187:       - value: python\n188:         label:\n189:           en_US: Python\n190:       - value: javascript\n191:         label:\n192:           en_US: JavaScript\n193:       - value: typescript\n194:         label:\n195:           en_US: TypeScript\n196:   - name: code\n197:     type: string\n198:     required: false\n199:     label:\n200:       en_US: Code\n201:     human_description:\n202:       en_US: Code to execute\n203:     llm_description: Source code string\n204:     form: llm\n205:   - name: command\n206:     type: string\n207:     required: false\n208:     label:\n209:       en_US: Command\n210:     human_description:\n211:       en_US: Shell command to execute\n212:     llm_description: Shell command string\n213:     form: llm\n214:   - name: session_id\n215:     type: string\n216:     required: false\n217:     label:\n218:       en_US: Session ID\n219:     human_description:\n220:       en_US: Existing session ID for reuse\n221:     llm_description: Session identifier for stateful execution\n222:     form: llm\n223:   - name: session_reuse\n224:     type: boolean\n225:     required: false\n226:     label:\n227:       en_US: Reuse Session\n228:     human_description:\n229:       en_US: Whether to reuse existing session\n230:     llm_description: Boolean flag for session reuse\n231:     form: llm\n232:   - name: code_interpreter_id\n233:     type: string\n234:     required: false\n235:     label:\n236:       en_US: Code Interpreter ID\n237:     human_description:\n238:       en_US: CodeInterpreter CR name\n239:     llm_description: Name of the CodeInterpreter resource\n240:     form: llm\n241: extra.python.source: tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py\n242: ```\n243: \n244: #### 8. `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n245: **Purpose**: Python tool implementation that delegates to AgentCube SDK.\n246: \n247: **Logic**:\n248: - Import `collections.abc.Generator`, `typing.Any`\n249: - Import `dify_plugin.Tool`, `dify_plugin.entities.tool.ToolInvokeMessage`\n250: - Import `agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient`\n251: - Define class `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool)`\n252: - Implement `_invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]`:\n253:   - Call `result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)`\n254:   - Yield `self.create_json_message(result)`\n255: - Implement `execute(self, router_url, workload_manager_url, language=\"python\", code_interpreter_id=None, session_id=None, code=None, command=None, session_reuse=False, **kwargs)`:\n256:   - Validate that at least one of `code` or `command` is provided (raise `ValueError` if neither)\n257:   - Instantiate `CodeInterpreterClient` with:\n258:     - `router_url=router_url`\n259:     - `workload_manager_url=workload_manager_url`\n260:     - `session_id=session_id` if provided\n261:   - Use context manager: `with client:`\n262:     - If `code` is provided: call `client.run_code(code, language=language)`\n263:     - If `command` is provided: call `client.execute_command(command)`\n264:   - Return result dict with `stdout`, `stderr`, `exit_code`, `duration` fields\n265:   - Handle exceptions: on `CommandExecutionError`, return result with error details\n266: \n267: #### 9. `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md`\n268: **Purpose**: Developer guide for installing and testing the Dify plugin.\n269: \n270: **Content**:\n271: - Installation steps (pip install requirements)\n272: - Local testing instructions\n273: - Packaging and deployment to Dify\n274: - Configuration requirements (router_url, workload_manager_url)\n275: \n276: #### 10. `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md`\n277: **Purpose**: User-facing documentation for the Dify plugin.\n278: \n279: **Content**:\n280: - Feature overview\n281: - Usage examples in Dify workflows\n282: - Parameter descriptions\n283: - Troubleshooting guide\n284: \n285: ---\n286: \n287: ## AR-025: PCAP Analyzer FastAPI Service\n288: \n289: ### Files to Create\n290: \n291: #### 11. `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py`\n292: **Purpose**: FastAPI application for PCAP analysis using AgentCube sandboxes.\n293: \n294: **Logic**:\n295: - **Imports**:\n296:   - `fastapi.FastAPI`, `UploadFile`, `File`, `Form`, `HTTPException`\n297:   - `pydantic.BaseModel`\n298:   - `uvicorn`\n299:   - `langchain_openai.ChatOpenAI`\n300:   - `langgraph.prebuilt.create_react_agent`\n301:   - `langchain_core.messages.HumanMessage`, `AIMessage`\n302:   - `agentcube.code_interpreter.CodeInterpreterClient`\n303:   - `agentcube.exceptions.CommandExecutionError`\n304:   - `os`, `tempfile`, `shutil`\n305: \n306: - **Configuration from environment**:\n307:   - `API_KEY = os.getenv(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")` (required)\n308:   - `API_BASE_URL = os.getenv(\"OPENAI_API_BASE\", \"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\")`\n309:   - `MODEL_NAME = os.getenv(\"OPENAI_MODEL\", \"Qwen/QwQ-32B\")`\n310:   - `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME = os.getenv(\"CODEINTERPRETER_NAME\", \"my-interpreter\")`\n311:   - `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE = os.getenv(\"SANDBOX_NAMESPACE\", \"default\")`\n312:   - `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC = int(os.getenv(\"SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC\", \"5\"))`\n313:   - `SERVER_HOST = \"0.0.0.0\"`, `SERVER_PORT = 8000`, `SERVER_RELOAD = True`\n314: \n315: - **Define `SandboxRunner` class**:\n316:   - `__init__(self, name, namespace, warmup_sec)`: store config, create `CodeInterpreterClient` later\n317:   - `upload_file(self, local_path, remote_path) -> bool`: use client to upload file\n318:   - `upload_bytes(self, data, remote_path) -> bool`: encode to base64, use client write\n319:   - `run(self, command) -> dict[str, Any]`: execute command via client, return result\n320:   - `stop(self)`: close client connection\n321: \n322: - **Define agent builders**:\n323:   - `build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)`: create ReAct agent with LangGraph\n324:   - `invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text) -> str`: run agent and extract response text\n325:   - `build_planner_agent(llm)`: build agent that plans PCAP analysis scripts\n326:   - `build_reporter_agent(llm)`: build agent that generates final reports\n327: \n328: - **Define orchestration functions**:\n329:   - `_plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path) -> str`: generate analysis plan\n330:   - `_repair_script(agent, prev_script, results) -> str`: repair failed script\n331:   - `_execute_once_in_runner(runner, pcap_local_path, script) -> list[dict]`: execute script steps\n332:   - `_analyze_with_retries(..., max_retries=2) -> dict`: orchestrate plan/execute/repair loop\n333:   - `_report(agent, results) -> str`: generate summary report\n334: \n335: - **Define `AnalyzeResponse` Pydantic model**:\n336:   - `script: str`\n337:   - `results: list[dict[str, Any]]`\n338:   - `report: str`\n339: \n340: - **Create FastAPI app**:\n341:   - `app = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer\")`\n342: \n343: - **Startup event**:\n344:   - `@app.on_event(\"startup\")`:\n345:     - Validate `API_KEY` is set, fail if missing\n346:     - Build `ChatOpenAI(api_key=API_KEY, base_url=API_BASE_URL, model=MODEL_NAME)`\n347:     - Initialize `PLANNER = build_planner_agent(llm)`\n348:     - Initialize `REPORTER = build_reporter_agent(llm)`\n349: \n350: - **POST `/analyze` endpoint**:\n351:   - Accept `pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None)` and `pcap_path: str = Form(None)`\n352:   - Validate at least one of `pcap_file` or `pcap_path` is provided\n353:   - If `pcap_file`: save to temp file\n354:   - Create `SandboxRunner` with config\n355:   - Try block:\n356:     - Call `_analyze_with_retries(...)`\n357:     - Call `_report(...)`\n358:     - Return `AnalyzeResponse(script=..., results=..., report=...)`\n359:   - Finally: call `runner.stop()`\n360:   - Handle exceptions: return `HTTPException(500, str(e))`\n361: \n362: - **Main block**:\n363:   - `uvicorn.run(app, host=SERVER_HOST, port=SERVER_PORT, reload=SERVER_RELOAD)`\n364: \n365: #### 12. `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n366: **Purpose**: Python dependencies for PCAP analyzer.\n367: \n368: **Content**:\n369: ```\n370: fastapi==0.120.0\n371: uvicorn==0.38.0\n372: python-multipart==0.0.20\n373: langchain==1.0.2\n374: langchain-classic==1.0.0\n375: langchain-community==0.4.1\n376: langchain-core==1.0.1\n377: langchain-openai==1.0.1\n378: langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0\n379: langgraph==1.0.1\n380: langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0\n381: langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1\n382: langgraph-sdk==0.2.9\n383: langsmith==0.4.38\n384: paramiko==4.0.0\n385: ```\n386: \n387: #### 13. `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile`\n388: **Purpose**: Container image for PCAP analyzer deployment.\n389: \n390: **Content**:\n391: ```dockerfile\n392: FROM ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim\n393: \n394: WORKDIR /app\n395: \n396: # Install uv and dependencies\n397: RUN uv venv\n398: COPY requirements.txt .\n399: RUN uv pip install -r requirements.txt\n400: \n401: # Vendor agentcube SDK from monorepo\n402: COPY sdk-python/agentcube ./agentcube/\n403: \n404: # Copy application\n405: COPY pcap_analyzer.py ./\n406: \n407: ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"\n408: EXPOSE 8000\n409: \n410: CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]\n411: ```\n412: \n413: #### 14. `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n414: **Purpose**: Kubernetes Deployment for PCAP analyzer.\n415: \n416: **Content**:\n417: ```yaml\n418: apiVersion: apps/v1\n419: kind: Deployment\n420: metadata:\n421:   name: pcap-analyzer\n422:   namespace: default\n423: spec:\n424:   replicas: 1\n425:   selector:\n426:     matchLabels:\n427:       app: pcap-analyzer\n428:   template:\n429:     metadata:\n430:       labels:\n431:         app: pcap-analyzer\n432:     spec:\n433:       containers:\n434:         - name: pcap-analyzer\n435:           image: pcap-analyzer:latest\n436:           imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n437:           ports:\n438:             - name: http\n439:               containerPort: 8000\n440:               protocol: TCP\n441:           resources:\n442:             requests:\n443:               cpu: 200m\n444:               memory: 100Mi\n445:             limits:\n446:               cpu: \"1\"\n447:               memory: 1Gi\n448:           env:\n449:             - name: OPENAI_API_KEY\n450:               valueFrom:\n451:                 secretKeyRef:\n452:                   name: pcap-analyzer-secrets\n453:                   key: openai-api-key\n454:             - name: OPENAI_API_BASE\n455:               value: \"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\"\n456:             - name: OPENAI_MODEL\n457:               value: \"Qwen/QwQ-32B\"\n458:             - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n459:               value: \"http://workloadmanager.default.svc.cluster.local:8080\"\n460:             - name: ROUTER_URL\n461:               value: \"http://agentcube-router.default.svc.cluster.local:8080\"\n462:             - name: CODEINTERPRETER_NAME\n463:               value: \"my-interpreter\"\n464:             - name: SANDBOX_NAMESPACE\n465:               value: \"default\"\n466:             - name: SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC\n467:               value: \"5\"\n468:           command: [\"uv\"]\n469:           args: [\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]\n470: ```\n471: \n472: #### 15. `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md`\n473: **Purpose**: Documentation for PCAP analyzer usage and deployment.\n474: \n475: **Content**:\n476: - Overview of PCAP analysis capabilities\n477: - Local development instructions\n478: - Kubernetes deployment guide\n479: - API endpoint documentation\n480: - Environment variable reference\n481: \n482: ---\n483: \n484: ## AR-026: Helm Chart — Workload Manager Templates\n485: \n486: ### Files to Create\n487: \n488: #### 16. `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml`\n489: **Purpose**: Helm chart metadata.\n490: \n491: **Content**:\n492: ```yaml\n493: apiVersion: v2\n494: name: agentcube\n495: description: AgentCube sandbox orchestration platform\n496: type: application\n497: version: 0.1.0\n498: appVersion: \"0.1.0\"\n499: keywords:\n500:   - agent\n501:   - sandbox\n502:   - kubernetes\n503: maintainers:\n504:   - name: volcano-sh\n505: home: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n506: ```\n507: \n508: #### 17. `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n509: **Purpose**: Default configuration values for the chart.\n510: \n511: **Content**:\n512: ```yaml\n513: # Global settings\n514: namespace: default\n515: \n516: # Redis configuration (required)\n517: redis:\n518:   addr: \"\"  # e.g., \"redis-master:6379\"\n519:   password: \"\"\n520: \n521: # Workload Manager configuration\n522: workloadmanager:\n523:   replicas: 1\n524:   image:\n525:     repository: agentcube/workloadmanager\n526:     tag: latest\n527:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n528:   service:\n529:     type: ClusterIP\n530:     port: 8080\n531:   resources:\n532:     requests:\n533:       cpu: 100m\n534:       memory: 256Mi\n535:     limits:\n536:       cpu: 500m\n537:       memory: 512Mi\n538:   healthCheck:\n539:     liveness:\n540:       path: /health\n541:       initialDelaySeconds: 10\n542:       periodSeconds: 10\n543:     readiness:\n544:       path: /health\n545:       initialDelaySeconds: 5\n546:       periodSeconds: 5\n547:   extraEnv: []\n548: \n549: # Router configuration\n550: router:\n551:   replicas: 1\n552:   image:\n553:     repository: agentcube/router\n554:     tag: latest\n555:     pullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n556:   service:\n557:     type: ClusterIP\n558:     port: 8080\n559:     targetPort: 8080\n560:   resources:\n561:     requests:\n562:       cpu: 100m\n563:       memory: 256Mi\n564:     limits:\n565:       cpu: 500m\n566:       memory: 512Mi\n567:   serviceAccountName: \"\"\n568:   debug: true\n569:   rbac:\n570:     create: false\n571: \n572: # Optional Volcano scheduler\n573: volcano:\n574:   scheduler:\n575:     enabled: false\n576:     image:\n577:       repository: volcano-sh/volcano-agent-scheduler\n578:       tag: latest\n579: \n580: # CRDs\n581: crds:\n582:   create: true\n583: ```\n584: \n585: #### 18. `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-deployment.yaml`\n586: **Purpose**: Workload Manager Deployment manifest.\n587: \n588: **Logic**:\n589: - Name: `workloadmanager`\n590: - Replicas from `.Values.workloadmanager.replicas`\n591: - Image from `.Values.workloadmanager.image`\n592: - Container ports: 8080\n593: - Environment variables:\n594:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from `.Values.redis.addr`\n595:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from `.Values.redis.password`\n596:   - Extra env from `.Values.workloadmanager.extraEnv`\n597: - Liveness probe: HTTP GET `.Values.workloadmanager.healthCheck.liveness.path`\n598: - Readiness probe: HTTP GET `.Values.workloadmanager.healthCheck.readiness.path`\n599: - Resources from `.Values.workloadmanager.resources`\n600: - ServiceAccount: `workloadmanager`\n601: \n602: #### 19. `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-service.yaml`\n603: **Purpose**: Workload Manager Service manifest.\n604: \n605: **Logic**:\n606: - Name: `workloadmanager`\n607: - Type from `.Values.workloadmanager.service.type`\n608: - Port from `.Values.workloadmanager.service.port`\n609: - Target port: 8080\n610: - Selector: `app: workloadmanager`\n611: \n612: #### 20. `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager-serviceaccount.yaml`\n613: **Purpose**: Workload Manager ServiceAccount.\n614: \n615: **Logic**:\n616: - Name: `workloadmanager`\n617: - Namespace: release namespace\n618: \n619: #### 21. `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager-clusterrole.yaml`\n620: **Purpose**: Workload Manager ClusterRole with required permissions.\n621: \n622: **Logic**:\n623: - Name: `workloadmanager`\n624: - Rules:\n625:   - API group `agents.x-k8s.io`: sandboxes (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete)\n626:   - API group `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io`: sandboxclaims (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete)\n627:   - API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`: agentruntimes, codeinterpreters (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete)\n628:   - API group `` (core): pods (get, list, watch), secrets (get, list, watch)\n629:   - API group `authentication.k8s.io`: tokenreviews (create)\n630: \n631: #### 22. `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager-clusterrolebinding.yaml`\n632: **Purpose**: Bind Workload Manager ServiceAccount to ClusterRole.\n633: \n634: **Logic**:\n635: - Name: `workloadmanager`\n636: - RoleRef: `ClusterRole/workloadmanager`\n637: - Subjects: `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace\n638: \n639: ---\n640: \n641: ## AR-027: Helm Chart — Router Templates\n642: \n643: ### Files to Create\n644: \n645: #### 23. `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-deployment.yaml`\n646: **Purpose**: Router Deployment manifest.\n647: \n648: **Logic**:\n649: - Name: `agentcube-router`\n650: - Replicas from `.Values.router.replicas`\n651: - Image from `.Values.router.image`\n652: - Container args: `--port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug` (if enabled)\n653: - Environment variables:\n654:   - `REDIS_ADDR` from `.Values.redis.addr`\n655:   - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from `.Values.redis.password`\n656:   - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n657: - ServiceAccount: from `.Values.router.serviceAccountName` or `agentcube-router`\n658: - Resources from `.Values.router.resources`\n659: \n660: #### 24. `manifests/charts/base/templates/router-service.yaml`\n661: **Purpose**: Router Service manifest.\n662: \n663: **Logic**:\n664: - Name: `agentcube-router`\n665: - Type: ClusterIP\n666: - Port from `.Values.router.service.port`\n667: - Target port from `.Values.router.service.targetPort`\n668: - Selector: `app: agentcube-router`\n669: \n670: #### 25. `manifests/charts/base/templates/router/rbac-serviceaccount.yaml`\n671: **Purpose**: Optional Router ServiceAccount (when RBAC enabled).\n672: \n673: **Logic**:\n674: - Conditional: `.Values.router.rbac.create`\n675: - Name: from `.Values.router.serviceAccountName` or `agentcube-router`\n676: \n677: #### 26. `manifests/charts/base/templates/router/rbac-role.yaml`\n678: **Purpose**: Optional Router Role for secret management.\n679: \n680: **Logic**:\n681: - Conditional: `.Values.router.rbac.create`\n682: - Name: `agentcube-router`\n683: - Namespace: release namespace\n684: - Rules: secrets (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete)\n685: \n686: #### 27. `manifests/charts/base/templates/router/rbac-rolebinding.yaml`\n687: **Purpose**: Bind Router ServiceAccount to Role.\n688: \n689: **Logic**:\n690: - Conditional: `.Values.router.rbac.create`\n691: - Name: `agentcube-router`\n692: - RoleRef: `Role/agentcube-router`\n693: - Subjects: ServiceAccount in release namespace\n694: \n695: ---\n696: \n697: ## AR-028: Helm Chart — CRDs and Optional Volcano Scheduler\n698: \n699: ### Files to Create\n700: \n701: #### 28. `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime-crd.yaml`\n702: **Purpose**: AgentRuntime CRD definition.\n703: \n704: **Content**:\n705: - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n706: - Version: `v1alpha1`\n707: - Kind: `AgentRuntime`\n708: - Scope: `Namespaced`\n709: - Subresources: `status`\n710: - AdditionalPrinterColumns: Age from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`\n711: - Spec schema: `Ports`, `Template` (SandboxTemplate), `SessionTimeout`, `MaxSessionDuration`\n712: \n713: #### 29. `manifests/charts/base/crds/codeinterpreter-crd.yaml`\n714: **Purpose**: CodeInterpreter CRD definition.\n715: \n716: **Content**:\n717: - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n718: - Version: `v1alpha1`\n719: - Kind: `CodeInterpreter`\n720: - Scope: `Namespaced`\n721: - Subresources: `status`\n722: - AdditionalPrinterColumns: Age from `.metadata.creationTimestamp`\n723: - Spec schema: `Ports`, `Template`, `SessionTimeout`, `MaxSessionDuration`, `WarmPoolSize`, `AuthMode`\n724: \n725: #### 30. `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano/scheduler-serviceaccount.yaml`\n726: **Purpose**: Volcano scheduler ServiceAccount.\n727: \n728: **Logic**:\n729: - Conditional: `.Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled`\n730: - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n731: \n732: #### 31. `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano/scheduler-configmap.yaml`\n733: **Purpose**: Volcano scheduler ConfigMap.\n734: \n735: **Logic**:\n736: - Conditional: `.Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled`\n737: - Configuration for Volcano agent scheduler\n738: \n739: #### 32. `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano/scheduler-clusterrole.yaml`\n740: **Purpose**: Volcano scheduler ClusterRole.\n741: \n742: **Logic**:\n743: - Conditional: `.Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled`\n744: - Permissions for pod scheduling\n745: \n746: #### 33. `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano/scheduler-clusterrolebinding.yaml`\n747: **Purpose**: Bind Volcano scheduler to ClusterRole.\n748: \n749: **Logic**:\n750: - Conditional: `.Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled`\n751: \n752: #### 34. `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano/scheduler-service.yaml`\n753: **Purpose**: Volcano scheduler Service.\n754: \n755: **Logic**:\n756: - Conditional: `.Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled`\n757: \n758: #### 35. `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano/scheduler-deployment.yaml`\n759: **Purpose**: Volcano scheduler Deployment.\n760: \n761: **Logic**:\n762: - Conditional: `.Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled`\n763: - Image from `.Values.volcano.scheduler.image`\n764: \n765: ---\n766: \n767: ## AR-029: Dockerfiles and Makefile Build Targets\n768: \n769: ### Files to Create/Modify\n770: \n771: #### 36. `docker/Dockerfile` (Workload Manager)\n772: **Purpose**: Multi-stage build for Workload Manager binary.\n773: \n774: **Content**:\n775: ```dockerfile\n776: # Build stage\n777: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n778: WORKDIR /build\n779: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n780: RUN go mod download\n781: COPY . .\n782: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n783: \n784: # Runtime stage\n785: FROM alpine:3.19\n786: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\n787: COPY --from=builder /workloadmanager /workloadmanager\n788: USER apiserver\n789: EXPOSE 8080\n790: ENTRYPOINT [\"/workloadmanager\"]\n791: ```\n792: \n793: #### 37. `docker/Dockerfile.router` (Router)\n794: **Purpose**: Multi-stage build for Router binary.\n795: \n796: **Content**:\n797: ```dockerfile\n798: # Build stage\n799: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n800: WORKDIR /build\n801: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n802: RUN go mod download\n803: COPY . .\n804: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /router ./cmd/router\n805: \n806: # Runtime stage\n807: FROM alpine:3.19\n808: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 router\n809: COPY --from=builder /router /router\n810: USER router\n811: EXPOSE 8080\n812: ENTRYPOINT [\"/router\"]\n813: ```\n814: \n815: #### 38. `docker/Dockerfile.picod` (PicoD)\n816: **Purpose**: Multi-stage build for PicoD binary.\n817: \n818: **Content**:\n819: ```dockerfile\n820: # Build stage\n821: FROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\n822: WORKDIR /build\n823: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n824: RUN go mod download\n825: COPY . .\n826: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /picod ./cmd/picod\n827: \n828: # Runtime stage\n829: FROM alpine:3.19\n830: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 picod\n831: COPY --from=builder /picod /picod\n832: USER picod\n833: EXPOSE 8080\n834: ENTRYPOINT [\"/picod\"]\n835: ```\n836: \n837: #### 39. `Makefile` (modify existing)\n838: **Purpose**: Build automation targets.\n839: \n840: **Targets to add/modify**:\n841: - `all`: default → `build`\n842: - `build`: generate → `bin/workloadmanager` from `./cmd/workload-manager`\n843: - `build-router`: `bin/router` from `./cmd/router`\n844: - `build-picod`: `bin/picod` from `./cmd/picod`\n845: - `test`: run Go tests with coverage\n846: - `docker-build`: build all Docker images\n847: - `docker-push`: push images to registry\n848: - `docker-workloadmanager`: build workload manager image\n849: - `docker-router`: build router image\n850: - `docker-picod`: build picod image\n851: - `generate`: run code generation\n852: - `gen-crd`: generate CRD manifests\n853: - `gen-client`: generate client-go code\n854: - `gen-all`: `generate` + `gen-crd` + `gen-client`\n855: - `gen-check`: verify generated files are up to date\n856: - `e2e`: run `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`\n857: - `e2e-clean`: clean up E2E test resources\n858: - `helm-lint`: lint Helm chart\n859: - `helm-template`: render Helm templates\n860: - `install`: deploy to cluster using Helm\n861: \n862: ---\n863: \n864: ## AR-030: GitHub Actions CI/CD Pipelines\n865: \n866: ### Files to Create\n867: \n868: #### 40. `.github/workflows/ci.yaml`\n869: **Purpose**: Continuous integration workflow.\n870: \n871: **Logic**:\n872: - Triggers: push to main, PRs to main\n873: - Jobs:\n874:   - `lint`: run `golangci-lint`, Python linting\n875:   - `test`: run Go tests with coverage\n876:   - `build`: build all binaries\n877:   - `helm-lint`: validate Helm chart\n878:   - `gen-check`: verify generated code is up to date\n879: \n880: #### 41. `.github/workflows/cd.yaml`\n881: **Purpose**: Continuous deployment workflow.\n882: \n883: **Logic**:\n884: - Triggers: tags matching `v*.*.*`\n885: - Jobs:\n886:   - `build-images`: build and push Docker images to registry\n887:   - `helm-release`: package and release Helm chart\n888:   - `publish-sdk`: publish Python SDK to PyPI\n889: \n890: #### 42. `.github/workflows/e2e.yaml`\n891: **Purpose**: E2E test workflow.\n892: \n893: **Logic**:\n894: - Triggers: push to main, PRs to main\n895: - Jobs:\n896:   - `e2e-tests`:\n897:     - Set up Kind cluster\n898:     - Deploy dependencies (Redis, Volcano)\n899:     - Install Helm chart\n900:     - Run Go E2E tests\n901:     - Run Python SDK E2E tests\n902:     - Upload test artifacts\n903: \n904: ---\n905: \n906: ## AR-031: CLI Toolkit — Pack and Build Commands\n907: \n908: ### Files to Create\n909: \n910: #### 43. `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`\n911: **Purpose**: Python CLI project metadata and dependencies.\n912: \n913: **Content**:\n914: ```toml\n915: [build-system]\n916: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n917: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n918: \n919: [project]\n920: name = \"kubectl-agentcube\"\n921: version = \"0.1.0\"\n922: description = \"AgentCube CLI for packaging and deploying AI agents\"\n923: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n924: dependencies = [\n925:     \"typer>=0.9.0\",\n926:     \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n927:     \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n928:     \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n929:     \"docker>=7.0.0\",\n930:     \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\",\n931:     \"requests>=2.31.0\",\n932: ]\n933: \n934: [project.scripts]\n935: agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n936: ```\n937: \n938: #### 44. `cmd/cli/agentcube/__init__.py`\n939: **Purpose**: Package initialization with version constant.\n940: \n941: **Content**:\n942: ```python\n943: __version__ = \"0.1.0\"\n944: __all__ = [\"__version__\"]\n945: ```\n946: \n947: #### 45. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n948: **Purpose**: Typer CLI application with subcommands.\n949: \n950: **Logic**:\n951: - Import `typer`, `logging`, `rich`\n952: - Define root callback with:\n953:   - `--version` (eager, Optional[bool]): print version and exit\n954:   - `--verbose` / `-v` (bool): enable debug logging\n955: - Create `app = typer.Typer()`\n956: - Register subcommands: `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`\n957: - Implement error handler `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)`:\n958:   - Print error message in red\n959:   - If verbose: print traceback\n960:   - Raise `typer.Exit(1)`\n961: \n962: #### 46. `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py`\n963: **Purpose**: Pydantic models for metadata validation.\n964: \n965: **Logic**:\n966: - Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model:\n967:   - `agent_name: str`\n968:   - `language: str` (validator: must be `python`, `java`, etc.)\n969:   - `entrypoint: str`\n970:   - `port: int` (validator: 1-65535)\n971:   - `build_mode: str` (validator: `local`, `cloud`)\n972:   - `version: str`\n973:   - `description: str`\n974:   - `router_url: str | None`\n975:   - `workload_manager_url: str | None`\n976:   - `agent_id: str | None`\n977:   - `session_id: str | None`\n978:   - `status: str | None`\n979: \n980: #### 47. `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n981: **Purpose**: Load and save agent metadata YAML.\n982: \n983: **Logic**:\n984: - Class `MetadataService`:\n985:   - `load_metadata(workspace_path) -> AgentMetadata`:\n986:     - Try `agent_metadata.yaml`, fall back to `agent.yaml`, then `metadata.yaml`\n987:     - Parse YAML, validate with Pydantic\n988:   - `save_metadata(metadata, workspace_path)`:\n989:     - Write to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n990:     - Use `yaml.dump` with proper formatting\n991:   - `update_metadata(metadata, updates)`: merge changes\n992: \n993: #### 48. `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n994: **Purpose**: Docker SDK wrapper for image operations.\n995: \n996: **Logic**:\n997: - Class `DockerService`:\n998:   - `check_docker_available()`: raise `RuntimeError` if Docker unavailable\n999:   - `build_image(workspace_path, image_name, tag, buildargs=None) -> dict`:\n1000:     - Use `docker.from_env()`\n1001:     - Call `docker.images.build()`\n1002:     - Return `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n1003:   - `push_image(image_name, registry_url=None, username=None, password=None) -> dict`:\n1004:     - Login if credentials provided\n1005:     - Retag if needed\n1006:     - Stream push logs\n1007:     - Return `pushed_image`, `push_time`\n1008:   - `remove_image(image_name) -> bool`: remove and handle errors\n1009: \n1010: #### 49. `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n1011: **Purpose**: Standard Kubernetes deployment provider.\n1012: \n1013: **Logic**:\n1014: - Class `KubernetesProvider`:\n1015:   - `__init__()`: initialize Kubernetes client\n1016:   - `deploy_agent(config) -> dict`:\n1017:     - Create/patch Deployment\n1018:     - Create/patch NodePort Service\n1019:     - Return deployment info\n1020:   - `wait_for_deployment_ready(deployment_name, namespace, timeout=120)`:\n1021:     - Poll deployment status\n1022:     - Raise `TimeoutError` on timeout\n1023:   - `delete_agent(deployment_name, namespace) -> dict`:\n1024:     - Delete Deployment and Service\n1025:     - Ignore 404 errors\n1026:   - `get_agent_status(deployment_name, namespace) -> dict`:\n1027:     - Return pod status\n1028: \n1029: #### 50. `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n1030: **Purpose**: AgentCube CRD provider.\n1031: \n1032: **Logic**:\n1033: - Class `AgentCubeProvider`:\n1034:   - `__init__()`: initialize Kubernetes client with custom API\n1035:   - `deploy_agent_runtime(config) -> dict`:\n1036:     - Build AgentRuntime CR object\n1037:     - Create/patch via CustomObjects API\n1038:     - Set env vars: `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`\n1039:     - Set `sessionTimeout: \"15m\"`, `maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"`\n1040:   - `get_agent_runtime_status(name, namespace) -> dict`:\n1041:     - Get CR from API\n1042:     - Extract status from `.status`\n1043:   - `delete_agent_runtime(name, namespace) -> dict`:\n1044:     - Delete CR, ignore 404\n1045: \n1046: #### 51. `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py`\n1047: **Purpose**: Pack command implementation.\n1048: \n1049: **Logic**:\n1050: - Class `PackRuntime`:\n1051:   - `__init__(metadata_overrides)`: store overrides\n1052:   - `pack(workspace_path) -> tuple[str, str]`:\n1053:     - Validate workspace exists and is directory\n1054:     - Validate language-specific requirements (Python: *.py files, Java: pom.xml)\n1055:     - Load or create metadata\n1056:     - Merge CLI overrides\n1057:     - Optionally generate Dockerfile\n1058:     - Save metadata\n1059:     - Return `(agent_name, metadata_path)`\n1060: \n1061: #### 52. `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n1062: **Purpose**: Build command implementation.\n1063: \n1064: **Logic**:\n1065: - Class `BuildRuntime`:\n1066:   - `__init__(proxy=None, cloud_provider=None)`: store config\n1067:   - `build(workspace_path) -> dict`:\n1068:     - Load metadata\n1069:     - Increment version (patch bump)\n1070:     - Check Docker availability for local build\n1071:     - Call `DockerService.build_image()`\n1072:     - Update metadata with image info\n1073:     - On failure: revert version\n1074:     - Return build result\n1075: \n1076: ---\n1077: \n1078: ## AR-032: CLI Toolkit — Publish, Invoke, Status Commands\n1079: \n1080: ### Files to Create\n1081: \n1082: #### 53. `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`\n1083: **Purpose**: Publish command implementation.\n1084: \n1085: **Logic**:\n1086: - Class `PublishRuntime`:\n1087:   - `__init__(provider, version=None, image_url=None, ...)`: store config\n1088:   - `publish(workspace_path) -> dict`:\n1089:     - Load metadata\n1090:     - If provider `agentcube`:\n1091:       - Validate `router_url` and `workload_manager_url` present\n1092:       - Use `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()`\n1093:     - If provider `k8s`:\n1094:       - Use `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()`\n1095:       - Wait for deployment ready\n1096:     - Update metadata with deployment info\n1097:     - Return publish result\n1098: \n1099: #### 54. `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n1100: **Purpose**: Invoke command implementation.\n1101: \n1102: **Logic**:\n1103: - Class `InvokeRuntime`:\n1104:   - `__init__(provider, headers=None)`: store config\n1105:   - `invoke(workspace_path, payload) -> dict`:\n1106:     - Load metadata\n1107:     - Build target URL:\n1108:       - If AgentRuntime CR: `{base}/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/`\n1109:       - Else: from metadata\n1110:     - Add headers:\n1111:       - `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` if session_id in metadata\n1112:       - Custom headers from CLI\n1113:     - POST JSON payload\n1114:     - Return response\n1115: \n1116: #### 55. `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n1117: **Purpose**: Status command implementation.\n1118: \n1119: **Logic**:\n1120: - Class `StatusRuntime`:\n1121:   - `__init__(provider)`: store config\n1122:   - `get_status(workspace_path) -> dict`:\n1123:     - Load metadata\n1124:     - If no `agent_id`: return `status=not_published`\n1125:     - If provider `agentcube`:\n1126:       - Call `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime_status()`\n1127:     - If provider `k8s`:\n1128:       - Call `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()`\n1129:     - Return status dict\n1130: \n1131: #### 56. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/pack.py`\n1132: **Purpose**: Pack subcommand definition.\n1133: \n1134: **Logic**:\n1135: - Define `@app.command(\"pack\")`:\n1136:   - Options: `workspace`, `agent_name`, `language`, `entrypoint`, `port`, `build_mode`, `description`, `output`, `verbose`\n1137:   - Use `Progress` spinner\n1138:   - Call `PackRuntime.pack()`\n1139:   - Print success or handle error\n1140: \n1141: #### 57. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/build.py`\n1142: **Purpose**: Build subcommand definition.\n1143: \n1144: **Logic**:\n1145: - Define `@app.command(\"build\")`:\n1146:   - Options: `workspace`, `proxy`, `cloud_provider`, `output`, `verbose`\n1147:   - Call `BuildRuntime.build()`\n1148:   - Print build result\n1149:   - Handle errors\n1150: \n1151: #### 58. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/publish.py`\n1152: **Purpose**: Publish subcommand definition.\n1153: \n1154: **Logic**:\n1155: - Define `@app.command(\"publish\")`:\n1156:   - Options: `workspace`, `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`, `verbose`\n1157:   - Call `PublishRuntime.publish()`\n1158:   - Print deployment info\n1159: \n1160: #### 59. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/invoke.py`\n1161: **Purpose**: Invoke subcommand definition.\n1162: \n1163: **Logic**:\n1164: - Define `@app.command(\"invoke\")`:\n1165:   - Options: `workspace`, `payload`, `header` (repeatable), `provider`, `verbose`\n1166:   - Parse payload as JSON (exit 1 if invalid)\n1167:   - Parse headers as `key:value` (exit 1 if invalid format)\n1168:   - Call `InvokeRuntime.invoke()`\n1169:   - Print response\n1170: \n1171: #### 60. `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/status.py`\n1172: **Purpose**: Status subcommand definition.\n1173: \n1174: **Logic**:\n1175: - Define `@app.command(\"status\")`:\n1176:   - Options: `workspace`, `provider`, `verbose`\n1177:   - Call `StatusRuntime.get_status()`\n1178:   - Display Rich Table with status info\n1179:   - Exit 1 if `not_published` or `error`\n1180: \n1181: ---\n1182: \n1183: ## AR-033: Python SDK — Clients and Exceptions\n1184: \n1185: ### Files to Create\n1186: \n1187: #### 61. `sdk-python/pyproject.toml`\n1188: **Purpose**: Python SDK project metadata.\n1189: \n1190: **Content**:\n1191: ```toml\n1192: [build-system]\n1193: requires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\", \"wheel\"]\n1194: build-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n1195: \n1196: [project]\n1197: name = \"agentcube-sdk\"\n1198: version = \"0.0.10\"\n1199: description = \"Python SDK for AgentCube sandbox orchestration\"\n1200: requires-python = \">=3.10\"\n1201: dependencies = [\n1202:     \"requests>=2.31.0\",\n1203: ]\n1204: \n1205: [project.optional-dependencies]\n1206: dev = [\n1207:     \"pytest>=7.0.0\",\n1208:     \"pytest-cov>=4.0.0\",\n1209: ]\n1210: ```\n1211: \n1212: #### 62. `sdk-python/agentcube/__init__.py`\n1213: **Purpose**: Package initialization with public API exports.\n1214: \n1215: **Content**:\n1216: ```python\n1217: from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n1218: from agentcube.agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n1219: \n1220: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n1221: ```\n1222: \n1223: #### 63. `sdk-python/agentcube/exceptions.py`\n1224: **Purpose**: Exception hierarchy for SDK errors.\n1225: \n1226: **Logic**:\n1227: - Define `AgentCubeError(Exception)`: base exception\n1228: - Define `CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError)`:\n1229:   - Constructor: `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`\n1230:   - Store as instance attributes\n1231: - Define `SessionError(AgentCubeError)`: session-related errors\n1232: - Define `DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError)`: data plane errors\n1233: \n1234: #### 64. `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n1235: **Purpose**: Workload Manager HTTP client.\n1236: \n1237: **Logic**:\n1238: - Class `ControlPlaneClient`:\n1239:   - `__init__(workload_manager_url, auth_token=None)`:\n1240:     - Resolve URL from arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env\n1241:     - Resolve token from arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n1242:     - Create `requests.Session` with connection pooling\n1243:     - Set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` if present\n1244:   - `create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600) -> str`:\n1245:     - POST to `/v1/code-interpreter`\n1246:     - JSON: `{name, namespace, ttl, metadata}`\n1247:     - Return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError`\n1248:   - `delete_session(session_id) -> bool`:\n1249:     - DELETE to `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}`\n1250:     - Return True on 404 or success, False on other errors\n1251: \n1252: #### 65. `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n1253: **Purpose**: Router data plane client for Code Interpreter.\n1254: \n1255: **Logic**:\n1256: - Class `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`:\n1257:   - `__init__(router_url, namespace, cr_name, session_id, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n1258:     - Build base URL using `urljoin`\n1259:     - Create `requests.Session`\n1260:     - Set default header `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n1261:   - `_request(method, path, **kwargs)`:\n1262:     - Add timeout tuple: `(connect_timeout, read_timeout)`\n1263:     - Raise on HTTP errors\n1264:   - `execute_command(command, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n1265:     - POST to `api/execute`\n1266:     - JSON: `{command: [...], timeout: \"<n>s\"}`\n1267:     - If `exit_code != 0`: raise `CommandExecutionError`\n1268:   - `write_file(path, content, mode=\"0644\")`:\n1269:     - POST to `api/files` with base64 content\n1270:   - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`:\n1271:     - Multipart POST to `api/files`\n1272:   - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`:\n1273:     - GET from `api/files/{path}`, stream to file\n1274:   - `list_files(path) -> list`:\n1275:     - GET from `api/files?path={path}`\n1276: \n1277: #### 66. `sdk-python/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n1278: **Purpose**: Router data plane client for Agent Runtime.\n1279: \n1280: **Logic**:\n1281: - Class `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`:\n1282:   - `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n1283:   - `__init__(router_url, namespace, agent_name, session_id, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n1284:     - Build invocation base URL\n1285:     - Create `requests.Session`\n1286:   - `_request(method, path, **kwargs)`:\n1287:     - Add timeout tuple\n1288:   - `invoke(payload, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n1289:     - POST JSON to invocation URL\n1290:     - Set `SESSION_HEADER` and `Content-Type`\n1291: \n1292: #### 67. `sdk-python/agentcube/code_interpreter.py`\n1293: **Purpose**: High-level Code Interpreter client.\n1294: \n1295: **Logic**:\n1296: - Class `CodeInterpreterClient`:\n1297:   - `__init__(router_url, workload_manager_url=None, name=None, namespace=\"default\", session_id=None, ttl=3600, timeout=120)`:\n1298:     - Validate `router_url` is provided (arg or `ROUTER_URL` env)\n1299:     - Store config\n1300:     - If `session_id` not provided:\n1301:       - Create `ControlPlaneClient`\n1302:       - Call `create_session()`\n1303:       - Handle failure: delete session, re-raise\n1304:     - Call `_init_data_plane()`\n1305:   - `_init_data_plane()`:\n1306:     - Create `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with session_id\n1307:   - `__enter__()`: return self\n1308:   - `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `stop()`\n1309:   - `stop()`:\n1310:     - Close data plane session\n1311:     - If created session: call `delete_session()`\n1312:     - Close control plane session\n1313:   - `execute_command(command, timeout=None) -> dict`: delegate to data plane\n1314:   - `run_code(code, language=\"python\") -> dict`:\n1315:     - Write timestamped `.py` file\n1316:     - Execute `python3 <file>`\n1317:   - `write_file(path, content)`: delegate\n1318:   - `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`: delegate\n1319:   - `download_file(remote_path, local_path)`: delegate\n1320:   - `list_files(path) -> list`: delegate\n1321: \n1322: #### 68. `sdk-python/agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n1323: **Purpose**: High-level Agent Runtime client.\n1324: \n1325: **Logic**:\n1326: - Class `AgentRuntimeClient`:\n1327:   - `__init__(router_url, namespace, agent_name, session_id=None, timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0)`:\n1328:     - Store config\n1329:     - If `session_id` not provided:\n1330:       - GET from invocation base URL\n1331:       - Read `x-agentcube-session-id` from response header\n1332:       - Raise `ValueError` if missing\n1333:     - Create `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n1334:   - `__enter__()`: return self\n1335:   - `__exit__(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb)`: call `close()`\n1336:   - `close()`: close underlying session\n1337:   - `invoke(payload, timeout=None) -> dict`:\n1338:     - If no session_id: raise `ValueError`\n1339:     - Delegate to data plane\n1340: \n1341: #### 69. `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py`\n1342: **Purpose**: HTTP utility functions.\n1343: \n1344: **Logic**:\n1345: - `read_token_from_file(path) -> str | None`:\n1346:   - Read file, return stripped contents\n1347:   - Handle FileNotFoundError, return None\n1348: - `create_session(timeout=120, connect_timeout=5.0) -> tuple`:\n1349:   - Create `requests.Session`\n1350:   - Mount `HTTPAdapter` with pool settings\n1351:   - Return session and timeout tuple\n1352: \n1353: #### 70. `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n1354: **Purpose**: General utility functions.\n1355: \n1356: **Logic**:\n1357: - `ensure_dir(path)`: create directory if not exists\n1358: - `generate_timestamp() -> str`: ISO format timestamp\n1359: - `base64_encode(data) -> str`: standard base64 encoding\n1360: - `base64_decode(s) -> bytes`: standard base64 decoding\n1361: \n1362: #### 71. `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py`\n1363: **Purpose**: Logging configuration.\n1364: \n1365: **Logic**:\n1366: - `setup_logging(level=logging.INFO)`:\n1367:   - Configure root logger with format\n1368:   - Return logger instance\n1369: \n1370: ---\n1371: \n1372: ## File Summary\n1373: \n1374: | File Count | Category |\n1375: |------------|----------|\n1376: | 10 | AR-023: Dify Plugin Manifest |\n1377: | 8 | AR-024: Dify Tool Schema |\n1378: | 5 | AR-025: PCAP Analyzer |\n1379: | 6 | AR-026: Helm Workload Manager |\n1380: | 5 | AR-027: Helm Router |\n1381: | 8 | AR-028: Helm CRDs & Volcano |\n1382: | 4 | AR-029: Dockerfiles & Makefile |\n1383: | 3 | AR-030: GitHub Actions |\n1384: | 10 | AR-031: CLI Pack/Build |\n1385: | 8 | AR-032: CLI Publish/Invoke/Status |\n1386: | 11 | AR-033: Python SDK |\n1387: | **Total: 78 files** |\n1388: \n1389: ---\n1390: \n1391: ## Implementation Phases\n1392: \n1393: ### Phase 1: Foundation (Week 1-2)\n1394: 1. **Python SDK (AR-033)**: Create core SDK clients and exceptions\n1395: 2. **Helm Chart Base (AR-026, AR-027, AR-028)**: Set up chart structure, CRDs, and base templates\n1396: 3. **Dockerfiles (AR-029)**: Create multi-stage builds for all Go binaries\n1397: \n1398: ### Phase 2: Integrations (Week 2-3)\n1399: 1. **Dify Plugin (AR-023, AR-024)**: Implement plugin manifest, provider, and tool schemas\n1400: 2. **CLI Toolkit (AR-031, AR-032)**: Build CLI commands for pack, build, publish, invoke, status\n1401: \n1402: ### Phase 3: Examples and CI/CD (Week 3-4)\n1403: 1. **PCAP Analyzer (AR-025)**: Create example FastAPI service\n1404: 2. **CI/CD Pipelines (AR-030)**: Set up GitHub Actions workflows\n1405: \n1406: ### Phase 4: Testing and Polish (Week 4-5)\n1407: 1. **Integration Tests**: End-to-end tests for all components\n1408: 2. **Documentation**: README files and guides\n1409: 3. **Performance Optimization**: Optimize bottlenecks\n1410: \n1411: ---\n1412: \n1413: ## Dependencies and Prerequisites\n1414: \n1415: ### External Dependencies\n1416: - Go 1.24+ for control plane components\n1417: - Python 3.10+ for SDK, CLI, and integrations\n1418: - Kubernetes 1.28+ cluster with CRD support\n1419: - Helm 3.x for chart installation\n1420: - Docker with Buildx for multi-arch images\n1421: - Redis 6+ for session storage\n1422: \n1423: ### Internal Dependencies\n1424: - SDK must be built before CLI and Dify plugin\n1425: - CRDs must exist before deploying Workload Manager/Router\n1426: - Helm chart must be complete before CI/CD pipelines\n1427: \n1428: ---\n1429: \n1430: ## Risk Mitigation\n1431: \n1432: ### High Priority Risks\n1433: 1. **Dify Plugin Compatibility**: Test against latest Dify version early\n1434: 2. **Kubernetes RBAC**: Verify ClusterRole permissions match actual usage\n1435: 3. **Session Management**: Ensure proper cleanup in SDK context managers\n1436: \n1437: ### Mitigation Strategies\n1438: - Implement comprehensive error handling in all clients\n1439: - Use connection pooling and timeouts for HTTP clients\n1440: - Add health checks and monitoring endpoints\n1441: - Create rollback procedures for deployments\n\n(End of file - total 1441 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Implementation Plan — AR-023 through AR-033\n\nThis plan maps Architectural Requirements AR-023 through AR-033 to specific files and implementation details based on the specifications in `./specs/`.\n\n## AR Mapping Overview\n\n| AR | Spec Domain | Package/Path | Description |\n|----|-------------|--------------|-------------|\n| AR-023 | integrations | `integrations/dify-plugin/` | Dify plugin manifest and provider structure |\n| AR-024 | integrations | `integrations/dify-plugin/` | Dify tool schema and implementation |\n| AR-025 | example | `example/pcap-analyzer/` | PCAP analyzer FastAPI service |\n| AR-026 | deployment | `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart templates for Workload Manager |\n| AR-027 | deployment | `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart templates for Router |\n| AR-028 | deployment | `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart RBAC and optional Volcano scheduler |\n| AR-029 | deployment | `docker/`, `Makefile` | Dockerfiles and build targets |\n| AR-030 | ci-cd | `.github/workflows/` | GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines |\n| AR-031 | cli-toolkit | `cmd/cli/agentcube/` | CLI pack/build commands |\n| AR-032 | cli-toolkit | `cmd/cli/agentcube/` | CLI publish/invoke/status commands |\n| AR-033 | python-sdk | `sdk-python/agentcube/` | SDK clients and exception hierarchy |\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"PLAN.md","time":{"start":1775899903471,"end":1775899903521}}}}
