{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899919879,"sessionID":"ses_2841e16f7ffeQo8aGKUpSQAL4X","part":{"id":"prt_d7be2441d001tHFPOx7YEZJSZo","messageID":"msg_d7be2290d001dHlPvBYOF6DtaD","sessionID":"ses_2841e16f7ffeQo8aGKUpSQAL4X","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c1b364b1d0bd4babaa047feae43f1fb9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/integrations/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/integrations/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Integrations — Design\n2: \n3: Sources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n4: \n5: ## Dify plugin — file map\n6: \n7: | File | Role |\n8: |------|------|\n9: | `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n10: | `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n11: | `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n12: | `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n13: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n14: | `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n15: | `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n16: | `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n17: \n18: ## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n19: \n20: From source:\n21: \n22: - `version`: `0.0.2`\n23: - `type`: `plugin`\n24: - `author`: `volcano-sh`\n25: - `name`: `agentcube`\n26: - `label`: map `en_US`, `ja_JP`, `zh_Hans`, `pt_BR` → `Agentcube`\n27: - `description`: multilingual strings (AgentCube description)\n28: - `icon`: `icon.png`\n29: - `icon_dark`: `icon-dark.png`\n30: - `resource`: `memory`, `permission` subtree (`tool`, `model`, `endpoint`, `app`, `storage` flags and sizes)\n31: - `plugins.tools`: list `[provider/agentcube.yaml]`\n32: - `meta`: `version`, `arch` (`amd64`, `arm64`), `runner` (`language: python`, `version: \"3.12\"`, `entrypoint: main`), `minimum_dify_version: null`\n33: - `created_at`, `privacy`, `repo`, `verified`\n34: \n35: ## `provider/agentcube.yaml` structure\n36: \n37: - `identity`: `author`, `name`, `label` (multilingual), `description` (multilingual), `icon`\n38: - Commented `oauth_schema` block (not active)\n39: - `tools`: list `[tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml]`\n40: - `extra.python.source`: `provider/agentcube.py`\n41: \n42: ## Tool definition (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`)\n43: \n44: - `identity.name`: `agentcube-code-interpreter`\n45: - `identity.author`: `agentcube`\n46: - `identity.label` / `description` (human + llm strings)\n47: - `parameters` (each has `name`, `type`, `required`, `label`, `human_description`, `llm_description`, `form`):\n48: \n49: | name | type | required | form | notes |\n50: |------|------|----------|------|-------|\n51: | `router_url` | string | true | form | |\n52: | `workload_manager_url` | string | true | form | |\n53: | `language` | select | false | llm | options: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript` |\n54: | `code` | string | false | llm | |\n55: | `command` | string | false | llm | |\n56: | `session_id` | string | false | llm | |\n57: | `session_reuse` | boolean | false | llm | |\n58: | `code_interpreter_id` | string | false | llm | |\n59: \n60: - `extra.python.source`: `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`\n61: \n62: ## Provider implementation (`provider/agentcube.py`)\n63: \n64: ```python\n65: from dify_plugin import ToolProvider\n66: from dify_plugin.errors.tool import ToolProviderCredentialValidationError\n67: \n68: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider(ToolProvider):\n69:     def _validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n70:         try:\n71:             \"\"\" IMPLEMENT YOUR VALIDATION HERE \"\"\"\n72:         except Exception as e:\n73:             raise ToolProviderCredentialValidationError(str(e))\n74: ```\n75: \n76: (OAuth helper methods are present only as comments.)\n77: \n78: ## Tool implementation (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py`)\n79: \n80: ```python\n81: from collections.abc import Generator\n82: from typing import Any\n83: from dify_plugin import Tool\n84: from dify_plugin.entities.tool import ToolInvokeMessage\n85: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n86: \n87: class AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool(Tool):\n88:     def _invoke(self, tool_parameters: dict[str, Any]) -> Generator[ToolInvokeMessage]:\n89:         result = self.execute(**tool_parameters)\n90:         yield self.create_json_message(result)\n91: \n92:     def execute(\n93:         self,\n94:         router_url=None,\n95:         workload_manager_url=None,\n96:         language=\"python\",\n97:         code_interpreter_id=None,\n98:         session_id=None,\n99:         code=None,\n100:         command=None,\n101:         session_reuse=False,\n102:         **kwargs\n103:     ): ...\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ## Plugin dependencies (`integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt`)\n107: \n108: ```\n109: dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0\n110: agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10\n111: ```\n112: \n113: ## PCAP analyzer — application structure (`example/pcap-analyzer/`)\n114: \n115: | File | Role |\n116: |------|------|\n117: | `pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI app, agents, sandbox runner, analysis orchestration, `uvicorn` entry |\n118: | `requirements.txt` | FastAPI, uvicorn, LangChain / LangGraph stack, multipart, etc. |\n119: | `Dockerfile` | `uv` base image, installs reqs, copies `sdk-python/agentcube` + `pcap_analyzer.py` |\n120: | `deployment.yaml` | K8s Deployment + env for OpenAI-compatible API and AgentCube URLs |\n121: | `README.md` | Documentation |\n122: \n123: ## FastAPI application (`pcap_analyzer.py`)\n124: \n125: ### Globals / config (selected)\n126: \n127: | Name | Source | Default / value |\n128: |------|--------|-----------------|\n129: | `API_KEY` | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | required at startup |\n130: | `API_BASE_URL` | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` |\n131: | `MODEL_NAME` | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` |\n132: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | env | `my-interpreter` |\n133: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | env | `default` |\n134: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | env | `5` |\n135: | `SERVER_HOST` | constant | `0.0.0.0` |\n136: | `SERVER_PORT` | constant | `8000` |\n137: | `SERVER_RELOAD` | constant | `True` |\n138: \n139: ### Core classes / functions\n140: \n141: ```python\n142: class SandboxRunner:\n143:     def __init__(self, name: str = \"my-interpreter\", namespace: str = \"default\", warmup_sec: int = 5): ...\n144:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n145:     def upload_bytes(self, data: bytes, remote_path: str) -> bool: ...\n146:     def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n147:     def stop(self): ...\n148: \n149: def build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str): ...\n150: def invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str: ...\n151: def build_planner_agent(llm): ...\n152: def build_reporter_agent(llm): ...\n153: \n154: def _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str: ...\n155: def _repair_script(agent, prev_script: str, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n156: def _execute_once_in_runner(runner: SandboxRunner, pcap_local_path: str, script: str) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n157: def _analyze_with_retries(..., max_retries: int = 2) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n158: def _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str: ...\n159: \n160: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n161:     script: str\n162:     results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n163:     report: str\n164: \n165: app = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer — Env-Only Config\")\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### FastAPI endpoints\n169: \n170: | Method | Path | Signature / behavior |\n171: |--------|------|----------------------|\n172: | (event) | startup | `on_startup()` → builds `ChatOpenAI`, `PLANNER`, `REPORTER`; fails if no API key |\n173: | `POST` | `/analyze` | `async def analyze_endpoint(pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None), pcap_path: str = Form(None))` → `response_model=AnalyzeResponse` |\n174: \n175: ### Imports of note\n176: \n177: ```python\n178: from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\n179: from pydantic import BaseModel\n180: import uvicorn\n181: from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n182: from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n183: from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\n184: from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n185: from agentcube.exceptions import CommandExecutionError\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ## Kubernetes deployment (`deployment.yaml`)\n189: \n190: - `Deployment` `pcap-analyzer` in `namespace: default`\n191: - Container `pcap-analyzer`, image `pcap-analyzer:latest`, `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n192: - Container port `8000` TCP\n193: - Resources: requests `cpu: 200m`, `memory: 100Mi`; limits `cpu: 1`, `memory: 1Gi`\n194: - Env: `OPENAI_API_KEY` from secret `pcap-analyzer-secrets` key `openai-api-key`; `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`, `ROUTER_URL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n195: - Command: `[\"uv\"]`, args: `[\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n196: \n197: ## Dockerfile highlights\n198: \n199: - Base: `ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim`\n200: - `uv venv` + `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`\n201: - Copies `sdk-python/agentcube` → `./agentcube/`, `pcap_analyzer.py` → `./`\n202: - `ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"`, exposes `8000`\n203: - `CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]`\n204: \n205: ## PCAP example Python dependencies (`example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`)\n206: \n207: Pinned packages include: `fastapi==0.120.0`, `uvicorn==0.38.0`, `langchain==1.0.2`, `langchain-classic==1.0.0`, `langchain-community==0.4.1`, `langchain-core==1.0.1`, `langchain-openai==1.0.1`, `langchain-text-splitters==1.0.0`, `langgraph==1.0.1`, `langgraph-checkpoint==3.0.0`, `langgraph-prebuilt==1.0.1`, `langgraph-sdk==0.2.9`, `langsmith==0.4.38`, `paramiko==4.0.0`, `python-multipart==0.0.20`\n208: \n209: *(The Dockerfile vendors `agentcube` from the monorepo copy; it is not listed in this `requirements.txt`.)*\n\n(End of file - total 209 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Integrations — Design\n\nSources: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/integrations/dify-plugin/`, `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`.\n\n## Dify plugin — file map\n\n| File | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `main.py` | `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()` |\n| `manifest.yaml` | Root plugin manifest for Dify |\n| `provider/agentcube.yaml` | Tool provider identity + tool list + Python entry |\n| `provider/agentcube.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` | Tool parameter schema |\n| `tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` | `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` |\n| `requirements.txt` | `dify-plugin` + `agentcube-sdk` pins |\n| `GUIDE.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, `.difyignore` | Docs / packaging |\n\n## `manifest.yaml` structure (exact top-level keys)\n\nFrom source:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/integrations/design.md","time":{"start":1775899919862,"end":1775899919878}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899919882,"sessionID":"ses_2841e16f7ffeQo8aGKUpSQAL4X","part":{"id":"prt_d7be2452c001z3dhpzYSrqR688","messageID":"msg_d7be2290d001dHlPvBYOF6DtaD","sessionID":"ses_2841e16f7ffeQo8aGKUpSQAL4X","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c67fcd59406e4bac9572520ee895e76b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Design\n2: \n3: Source tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n4: \n5: ## Chart.yaml\n6: \n7: | Field | Value |\n8: |--------|--------|\n9: | `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n10: | `name` | `agentcube` |\n11: | `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n12: | `version` | `0.1.0` |\n13: | `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n14: \n15: ## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n16: \n17: | Path | Type | Default |\n18: |------|------|---------|\n19: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n20: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n21: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n22: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` |\n23: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n24: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n25: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` |\n26: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n27: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n28: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n29: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n30: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` |\n31: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n32: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n33: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n34: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n35: | `router.config` | object | `{}` |\n36: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n37: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` |\n38: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n39: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n40: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` |\n41: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n42: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n43: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n44: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n45: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n46: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n47: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n48: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n49: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n50: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n51: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` |\n52: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` |\n53: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n54: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n55: \n56: Comments in `values.yaml` state Redis settings “must be provided by the user during installation”; defaults are still empty strings.\n57: \n58: ## Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\n59: \n60: ### `workloadmanager.yaml`\n61: \n62: | Kind | Name | Namespace | Notes |\n63: |------|------|-----------|--------|\n64: | `Deployment` | `workloadmanager` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` | `replicas`: `workloadmanager.replicas`; `serviceAccountName`: `workloadmanager`; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `workloadmanager`; image `repository:tag`; `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` → `workloadmanager.service.port`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_ADDR`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); **resources**: from values; **liveness/readiness**: HTTP GET `/health` on service port, delays 10s/10s and 5s/5s |\n65: | `Service` | `workloadmanager` | release ns | `type`: `workloadmanager.service.type`; port & `targetPort`: `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager` |\n66: \n67: ### `agentcube-router.yaml`\n68: \n69: | Kind | Name | Notes |\n70: |------|------|--------|\n71: | `Deployment` | `agentcube-router` | `replicas`: `router.replicas`; **conditional** `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` non-empty; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `agentcube-router`; image from `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`; **resources** from values; **liveness** `/health/live`, **readiness** `/health/ready` on targetPort, 1s initial, 2s period |\n72: | `Service` | `agentcube-router` | `type` `router.service.type`; `port` `router.service.port`, `targetPort` `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router` |\n73: \n74: ### `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n75: \n76: | Kind | Name | Scope | Notes |\n77: |------|------|-------|--------|\n78: | `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | release namespace | — |\n79: | `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | rules below |\n80: | `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | binds `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` to `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace |\n81: \n82: ### `rbac-router.yaml`\n83: \n84: Rendered **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true.\n85: \n86: | Kind | Name pattern | Notes |\n87: |------|--------------|--------|\n88: | `ServiceAccount` | `{{ router.serviceAccountName \\| default \"agentcube-router\" }}` | release namespace |\n89: | `Role` | same as SA name | rules: `secrets` in `\"\"` apiGroup, full verb set `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n90: | `RoleBinding` | same | subject: SA above; `Role` ref same name |\n91: \n92: ### `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n93: \n94: Rendered **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled`.\n95: \n96: Creates (in order in file): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers predicates/nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (large rule set — see RBAC section); `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080 metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with `replicas` from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from values, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, volumes for config + emptyDir.\n97: \n98: ## RBAC rules (exact apiGroups / resources / verbs)\n99: \n100: ### ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n101: \n102: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n103: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n104: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n105: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n106: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n107: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n108: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n109: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n110: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n111: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n112: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n113: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n114: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n115: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n116: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n117: \n118: ### Role `router` (optional)\n119: \n120: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n121: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n122: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n123: \n124: ### ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` (when enabled)\n125: \n126: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n127: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n128: | `apiextensions.k8s.io` | `customresourcedefinitions` | `create,get,list,watch,delete` |\n129: | `\"\"` | `events` | `create,list,watch,update,patch` |\n130: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch,patch,delete` |\n131: | `\"\"` | `pods/status` | `update` |\n132: | `\"\"` | `pods/binding` | `create` |\n133: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumeclaims` | `list,watch,update` |\n134: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumes` | `list,watch,update` |\n135: | `\"\"` | `namespaces,services,replicationcontrollers` | `list,watch,get` |\n136: | `\"\"` | `resourcequotas` | `list,watch` |\n137: | `\"\"` | `nodes` | `get,list,watch,update,patch` |\n138: | `storage.k8s.io` | `storageclasses,csinodes,csidrivers,csistoragecapacities,volumeattachments` | `list,watch` |\n139: | `policy` | `poddisruptionbudgets` | `list,watch` |\n140: | `scheduling.k8s.io` | `priorityclasses` | `get,list,watch` |\n141: | `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io`, `scheduling.volcano.sh` | `podgroups` | `list,watch,update` |\n142: | `\"\"` | `configmaps` | `get,list,watch,create,delete,update` |\n143: | `apps` | `daemonsets,replicasets,statefulsets` | `list,watch,get` |\n144: | `coordination.k8s.io` | `leases` | `get,create,update,watch` |\n145: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch` |\n146: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims/status` | `update` |\n147: | `resource.k8s.io` | `deviceclasses,resourceslices` | `get,list,watch,create` |\n148: | `shard.volcano.sh` | `nodeshards` | `list,watch,get,update` |\n149: \n150: ## CRD definitions shipped (`manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n151: \n152: | File | CRD `metadata.name` | group | versions | scope | Notes |\n153: |------|---------------------|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n154: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` (served+storage); printer column Age | `Namespaced` | `openAPIV3Schema` includes root fields `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`, `status`. **spec.required**: `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`. **Key spec fields**: `maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`); `sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`); `targetPort` (array of port objects: required `port`, `protocol` enum HTTP/HTTPS, optional `name`, `pathPrefix`); `podTemplate` (annotations, labels, nested `spec` = full PodSpec-shaped schema). **status**: conditions, etc. Annotation `controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2` |\n155: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `Namespaced` | **spec** includes `authMode` enum `picod|none` default `picod`; `maxSessionDuration` default `8h`; `sessionTimeout` default `15m`; `ports` (same TargetPort shape as above); `template` (image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.); optional `warmPoolSize` int32. **spec.required**: `template`. **status**: `conditions`, `ready`; subresource `status`. Same controller-gen version annotation |\n156: \n157: ## Dockerfiles\n158: \n159: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (workloadmanager)\n160: \n161: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n162: |-------|------|---------|\n163: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | `WORKDIR /workspace`; copy `go.mod`/`go.sum`; `go mod download`; copy `cmd/`, `pkg/`; build `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` with BuildKit cache mounts |\n164: | runtime | `alpine:3.19` | `apk add ca-certificates`; `WORKDIR /app`; copy binary; `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`; `USER apiserver`; `EXPOSE 8080`; `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`; `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]` |\n165: \n166: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux`, `TARGETARCH` (implicit platform).\n167: \n168: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n169: \n170: Same pattern as workloadmanager builder, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/`; output binary `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`; runtime user `router` UID 1000; `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`.\n171: \n172: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n173: \n174: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n175: |-------|------|---------|\n176: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` | `WORKDIR /app`; copy mod files; download; `COPY . .`; build `picod` from `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n177: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` | `apt-get install -y python3`; `WORKDIR /root/`; copy binary; **runs as root** (comment: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions); `ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]` |\n178: \n179: ## Makefile — variables (key)\n180: \n181: | Variable | Default / definition |\n182: |----------|----------------------|\n183: | `HUB` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` |\n184: | `TAG` | `latest` |\n185: | `PROJECT_DIR` | directory of Makefile |\n186: | `GOBIN` | from `go env` |\n187: | `CONTAINER_TOOL` | `docker` |\n188: | `SHELL` | `/usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail` |\n189: | `LOCALBIN` | `$(shell pwd)/bin` |\n190: | `CONTROLLER_GEN` | `$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen` |\n191: | `GOLANGCI_LINT` | `$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint` |\n192: | `CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION` | `v0.17.2` |\n193: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `v1.64.1` |\n194: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n195: | `ROUTER_IMAGE` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n196: | `PICOD_IMAGE` | `picod:latest` |\n197: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `\"\"` |\n198: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` |\n199: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_REPO` | `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox.git` |\n200: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `main` (Makefile comment; E2E script overrides — see CI design) |\n201: \n202: ## Makefile — targets\n203: \n204: | Target | Depends / notes |\n205: |--------|-----------------|\n206: | `all` | → `build` |\n207: | `help` | awk help from `##` comments |\n208: | `gen-crd` | `controller-gen`; `crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` → `manifests/charts/base/crds` |\n209: | `generate` | `controller-gen object` + `gen-crd` + `go mod tidy` |\n210: | `gen-client` | `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`; `go mod tidy` |\n211: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n212: | `gen-check` | `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code` |\n213: | `build` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` |\n214: | `build-agentd` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` |\n215: | `build-router` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` |\n216: | `build-all` | `build` + `build-agentd` + `build-router` |\n217: | `run` | `go run ./cmd/workload-manager/main.go --port=8080 --ssh-username=sandbox --ssh-port=22` |\n218: | `run-local` | same with `--kubeconfig=${HOME}/.kube/config` |\n219: | `run-router` | `go run ./cmd/router/main.go --port=8080 --debug` |\n220: | `clean` | `rm -rf bin/` and root binaries |\n221: | `deps` | `go mod download`; `go mod tidy` |\n222: | `update-deps` | `go get -u ./...`; `go mod tidy` |\n223: | `test` | `go test -v ./...` |\n224: | `fmt` | `go fmt ./...` |\n225: | `vet` | `go vet ./...` |\n226: | `lint` | `$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...` |\n227: | `gen-copyright` | `hack/update-copyright.sh` |\n228: | `install` | `build` + `sudo cp bin/workloadmanager /usr/local/bin/` |\n229: | `docker-build` | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n230: | `docker-buildx` | buildx linux/amd64,arm64 |\n231: | `docker-buildx-push` | requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY`; buildx `--push` |\n232: | `docker-push` | tag+push workloadmanager |\n233: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE)` |\n234: | `docker-build-router` / `docker-buildx-router` / `docker-buildx-push-router` / `docker-push-router` / `kind-load-router` | same pattern for router image |\n235: | `docker-build-picod` / `docker-buildx-picod` / `docker-buildx-push-picod` / `docker-push-picod` | same for picod |\n236: | `controller-gen` / `golangci-lint` | download via `go-install-tool` macro |\n237: | `e2e` | `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n238: | `e2e-clean` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n239: | `build-python-sdk` | copy `LICENSE` to `sdk-python`, `python3 -m build` in `sdk-python`, remove copied LICENSE |\n240: \n241: ## hack/ scripts\n242: \n243: | File | Purpose |\n244: |------|---------|\n245: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | Runs `k8s.io/code-generator` **v0.34.1**: sources `kube_codegen.sh`, calls `kube::codegen::gen_client --with-watch --output-dir client-go --output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go --boilerplate hack/boilerplate.go.txt --one-input-api runtime/v1alpha1` on `pkg/apis`; post-processes lister files with `sed` to append `.GroupResource()` for codeinterpreter/agentruntime resources |\n246: | `hack/update-copyright.sh` | Prepends Apache/Volcano boilerplate to `*.go` and `*.py` under git root (excluding vendor/venv) if missing “Copyright The Volcano Authors”; uses `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` / `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`; requires `sponge` (moreutils) |\n247: | `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` | Go file header template |\n248: | `hack/boilerplate.py.txt` | Python file header template |\n249: \n250: ## Helm / E2E reference command (from `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n251: \n252: Illustrative install used in E2E:\n253: \n254: ```bash\n255: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n256:   --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n257:   --create-namespace \\\n258:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n259:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n260:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n261:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n262:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n263:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n264:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n265:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n266:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n267:   --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n268:   --wait\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Images are expected to be loaded into Kind with local names `workloadmanager:latest`, `agentcube-router:latest`, `picod:latest` after `make docker-build` variants.\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Design\n\nSource tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n\n## Chart.yaml\n\n| Field | Value |\n|--------|--------|\n| `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n| `name` | `agentcube` |\n| `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n| `version` | `0.1.0` |\n| `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n\n## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"specs/deployment/design.md","time":{"start":1775899919865,"end":1775899919880}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899919885,"sessionID":"ses_2841e16f7ffeQo8aGKUpSQAL4X","part":{"id":"prt_d7be245ce001jA1k1ZZR7uvIHT","messageID":"msg_d7be2290d001dHlPvBYOF6DtaD","sessionID":"ses_2841e16f7ffeQo8aGKUpSQAL4X","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4b45dd9793d044acb064514b6cdd7230","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # SDD-TEE v5.1 — SDD Token Efficiency Evaluation\n2: \n3: 基于 **CodeSpec 工作流** 与 **OpenSpec OPSX 工具链**的 AI Coding Assistant Token 效率评估框架。\n4: \n5: 通过将真实开源项目 [agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube) 拆解为 **43 个细粒度 AR（分配需求）**，\n6: 每个 AR 走完整的 SDD 流程（`/opsx:new` → `/opsx:ff` → `/opsx:apply` → `/opsx:verify` → `/opsx:archive`），\n7: **量化 8 个阶段（ST-0~ST-7）× 5 个维度的 Token 消耗**，为 Token 提效研究提供评估基线。\n8: \n9: ## v5.1 架构\n10: \n11: ```\n12: engine.py (benchmark driver)\n13:   → adapters/*.py (CLI tool subprocess)\n14:     → LiteLLM Proxy JSONL (authoritative token log, port 4000)\n15:       → auditor.py (time-window filtering, cost calculation)\n16:         → _full.json (schema-compliant output)\n17: ```\n18: \n19: **核心特性**:\n20: - **LiteLLM Proxy 为唯一权威数据源**: 每次 API 调用均记录精确 token 用量\n21: - **Native CLI 兜底解析**: 适配器从 CLI 工具输出中解析 token，作为 Proxy 不可用时的回退\n22: - **Reconciliation 机制**: 每完成一个 AR 后重新解析全部日志，修正 api_calls 膨胀\n23: - **零伪造数据**: dry-run 模式仅打印 prompt，绝不估算 token\n24: \n25: ## 8 阶段工作流\n26: \n27: | 阶段 | 名称 | 说明 |\n28: |------|------|------|\n29: | ST-0 | AR 输入 | 读取 AR 描述文件，构建上下文 |\n30: | ST-1 | 需求澄清 | 模型理解需求、提出澄清问题 |\n31: | ST-2 | Spec 增量设计 | 生成/修改 OpenSpec 规格文件 |\n32: | ST-3 | Design 增量设计 | 生成/修改设计文档 |\n33: | ST-4 | 任务拆解 | 将设计分解为可执行任务列表 |\n34: | ST-5 | 开发实现 | 实际代码编写与修改 |\n35: | ST-6 | 一致性验证 | 验证实现与 Spec/Design 一致性 |\n36: | ST-6.5 | 原始代码等价性验证 | 确保不破坏原有功能 |\n37: | ST-7 | 合并归档 | 将变更合并至主分支并归档 |\n38: \n39: ## 5 维指标体系\n40: \n41: | 维度 | 编码 | 指标示例 |\n42: |------|------|----------|\n43: | 阶段维度 | ST-0 ~ ST-7 | 各阶段 Input/Output/Cache Tokens、迭代数、耗时 |\n44: | 角色维度 | RT-AI / RT-HUMAN | AI Token、人工输入 Token、人机比、预制规范（单独标注） |\n45: | 效率维度 | ET-LOC / ET-FILE / ET-TASK | Token/LOC、Token/File、Token/Task、Token/AR |\n46: | 质量维度 | QT-COV / QT-CONSIST | Token/覆盖率、Token/一致性、Token/可用率、Token/Bug |\n47: | 分布维度 | PT-DESIGN / PT-DEV | 设计/开发/验证阶段占比、峰值阶段 |\n48: \n49: ## 快速开始\n50: \n51: ```bash\n52: # 1. 环境初始化\n53: make setup\n54: \n55: # 2. 环境预检\n56: make preflight TOOL=opencode-cli MODEL=bailian-coding-plan/qwen3.6-plus\n57: \n58: # 3. 运行单次评测\n59: make run-v51 TOOL=opencode-cli MODEL=bailian-coding-plan/qwen3.6-plus\n60: \n61: # 3b. 通过 LiteLLM Proxy 运行（推荐，token 数据更精确）\n62: make run-v51-proxy TOOL=claude-code MODEL=claude-sonnet-4\n63: \n64: # 3c. Dry-run 模式（仅测试 prompt，不发起真实 API 调用）\n65: make run-v51-dry TOOL=opencode-cli MODEL=bailian-coding-plan/qwen3.6-plus\n66: \n67: # 4. 批量评测（所有默认组合）\n68: make batch-v51\n69: \n70: # 5. 生成报告\n71: make report-v51                              # 最新运行的报告\n72: make compare-v51                             # 跨 run 横向对比\n73: make export-v51                              # 导出 CSV/JSON/Markdown\n74: make selftest                                # schema 校验\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ## CLI 适配器与 Token 追踪\n78: \n79: v5.1 为每个 CLI 工具提供专用适配器，支持两种 token 数据来源：\n80: \n81: | 工具 | 原生解析方式 | Proxy 路由 | data_source |\n82: |------|-------------|------------|-------------|\n83: | claude-code | `--output-format json` NDJSON | `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` | litellm_proxy |\n84: | gemini-cli | `step_finish` 事件 | 部分支持 | litellm_proxy |\n85: | cursor-cli | N/A | Provider 依赖 | litellm_proxy |\n86: | opencode-cli | `step_finish` JSONL | Provider 依赖 | litellm_proxy |\n87: \n88: **数据优先级**: `litellm_proxy` > `native_output` > `none`\n89: - 当 Proxy 可用时，使用 auditor.py 按时间窗口过滤 JSONL 日志，获取精确 per-stage token\n90: - 当 Proxy 不可用时，适配器从 CLI 输出中解析 token（可能不完整）\n91: - 若两者均不可用，该 stage 的 token 数据为 0，**不会估算或伪造**\n92: \n93: ## 模型定价与成本分析\n94: \n95: 以下价格来自各 provider 官方定价页（每 1M tokens，USD）：\n96: \n97: | 模型 | Input | Output | Cache Read | Cache Write | 实测 ~$/AR |\n98: |------|-------|--------|------------|-------------|------------|\n99: | claude-sonnet-4 | $3.00 | $15.00 | $0.30 | $3.75 | ~$0.50 |\n100: | claude-4.6-opus-high-thinking | $15.00 | $75.00 | $1.50 | $18.75 | ~$2.50 |\n101: | gemini-3.1-pro | $1.25 | $10.00 | $0.10 | $1.50 | ~$0.40 |\n102: | gemini-2.5-pro | $1.25 | $10.00 | $0.10 | $1.50 | ~$0.40 |\n103: | gpt-4.1 | $2.00 | $8.00 | $0.25 | $2.50 | ~$0.35 |\n104: | glm-5 | $0.50 | $2.00 | $0.10 | $0.50 | ~$0.35 |\n105: | glm-4.7 | $0.50 | $2.00 | $0.10 | $0.50 | ~$0.35 |\n106: | kimi-k2.5 | $0.50 | $2.00 | $0.10 | $0.50 | ~$0.32 |\n107: | minimax-m2.5 | $0.50 | $2.00 | $0.10 | $0.50 | ~$0.35 |\n108: | qwen3.5-plus | $0.50 | $2.00 | $0.10 | $0.50 | ~$0.32 |\n109: | qwen3.6-plus | — | — | — | — | ~$0.88 |\n110: \n111: > ~$/AR 基于实际 benchmark 遥测数据。支持 Context Caching 的模型（如 qwen3.5-plus、kimi-k2.5）\n112: > 可节省 70%+ 的 input token 成本；不支持 Caching 的模型（如 qwen3.6-plus）成本较高。\n113: \n114: ## 并行评测\n115: \n116: v5.1 支持同时运行多个不同模型的 benchmark，各 run 之间完全隔离：\n117: \n118: - **Workspace 隔离**: 每个 run 使用独立的 `{run_id}_logs/` 目录\n119: - **模型隔离**: 通过 `--model` CLI 参数指定，无全局状态共享\n120: - **认证隔离**: opencode 使用 `~/.local/share/opencode/auth.json` 按 provider 存储\n121: - **日志隔离**: 每个 run 输出到独立的 `_full.json` 文件\n122: \n123: **并行运行示例**:\n124: ```bash\n125: # 终端 1\n126: make run-v51 TOOL=opencode-cli MODEL=bailian-coding-plan/glm-5\n127: \n128: # 终端 2\n129: make run-v51 TOOL=opencode-cli MODEL=bailian-coding-plan/kimi-k2.5\n130: \n131: # 终端 3\n132: make run-v51 TOOL=opencode-cli MODEL=bailian-coding-plan/qwen3.5-plus\n133: ```\n134: \n135: **注意事项**:\n136: - 所有模型共享同一个 API Key（`bailian-coding-plan`），需注意 rate limit\n137: - 建议同时运行的模型数 ≤ 6，避免 API 限流\n138: - 系统资源：6 个并发 benchmark 约消耗 ~8.2GB 内存（16GB 系统），已配置 4GB swap 防 OOM\n139: \n140: ## 数据完整性保障\n141: \n142: | 保障层 | 机制 | 验证命令 |\n143: |--------|------|----------|\n144: | **Reconciliation** | 每完成一个 AR 后重新解析全部日志，修正 api_calls 膨胀 | 自动执行 |\n145: | **数据合约** | `schema.py` 定义全部核心指标，报告生成前强制校验 | `make selftest` |\n146: | **环境预检** | `preflight.py` 检查依赖、工具链、API 连通性 | `make preflight` |\n147: | **零伪造** | dry-run 仅打印 prompt，不估算 token | `make run-v51-dry` |\n148: \n149: ## 目录结构\n150: \n151: ```\n152: sdd-tee/\n153: ├── Makefile                    # 统一入口（所有操作通过 make 触发）\n154: ├── configs/\n155: │   └── litellm_config.yaml     # LiteLLM Proxy 路由配置\n156: ├── specs/                      # 43 个 AR 规格文件\n157: ├── scripts/\n158: │   ├── engine.py               # 主 benchmark 驱动 (v5.1)\n159: │   ├── auditor.py              # LiteLLM JSONL token 审计器\n160: │   ├── schema.py               # 数据 schema 校验\n161: │   ├── report.py               # HTML 报告生成\n162: │   ├── compare.py              # 跨 run 横向对比\n163: │   ├── export.py               # CSV/JSON/Markdown 导出\n164: │   ├── preflight.py            # 环境验证\n165: │   ├── run_benchmark.sh        # 单次评测入口\n166: │   ├── batch_benchmark.sh      # 批量评测入口\n167: │   └── adapters/\n168: │       ├── base.py             # StageRecord + BaseAdapter 基类\n169: │       ├── claude_code.py      # Claude Code 适配器\n170: │       ├── gemini_cli.py       # Gemini CLI 适配器\n171: │       ├── cursor_cli.py       # Cursor CLI 适配器\n172: │       └── opencode_cli.py     # OpenCode CLI 适配器\n173: ├── workspaces/                 # 按 run 隔离的代码工作区\n174: └── results/\n175:     ├── runs/v5.1/              # _full.json + 日志备份\n176:     └── reports/v5.1/           # HTML 报告与对比看板\n177: ```\n178: \n179: ## License\n180: \n181: MIT\n\n(End of file - total 181 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# SDD-TEE v5.1 — SDD Token Efficiency Evaluation\n\n基于 **CodeSpec 工作流** 与 **OpenSpec OPSX 工具链**的 AI Coding Assistant Token 效率评估框架。\n\n通过将真实开源项目 [agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube) 拆解为 **43 个细粒度 AR（分配需求）**，\n每个 AR 走完整的 SDD 流程（`/opsx:new` → `/opsx:ff` → `/opsx:apply` → `/opsx:verify` → `/opsx:archive`），\n**量化 8 个阶段（ST-0~ST-7）× 5 个维度的 Token 消耗**，为 Token 提效研究提供评估基线。\n\n## v5.1 架构\n\n```\nengine.py (benchmark driver)\n  → adapters/*.py (CLI tool subprocess)\n    → LiteLLM Proxy JSONL (authoritative token log, port 4000)\n      → auditor.py (time-window filtering, cost calculation)\n        → _full.json (schema-compliant output)\n```\n\n**核心特性**:\n- **LiteLLM Proxy 为唯一权威数据源**: 每次 API 调用均记录精确 token 用量","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1775899919867,"end":1775899919883}}}}
